<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Korea-Mission     03-04 0130</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Korea-Mission,0133</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>South Korea's Buying Mission To Visit U.S. In May</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEOUL, South Korea (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   South Korea plans to send a buying
mission to the United States in May as part of its effort to ease
growing trade frictions with Washington, government and industry
officials said today.
   The mission, to be headed by Nam Duck-woo, president of the
Korea Foreign Trade Association, will tour various U.S. cities for
15 days to purchase machinery and other industrial products, the
officials said.
   Officials did not give details of the mission's itinerary or
shopping list.
   The United States has pressured South Korea to open its markets
wider to American products to cut its growing trade surplus. The
United States ran a trade deficit of $9.5 billion with South Korea
last year.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
