<HEAD>Bush Endorsed by Former US Attorney General Elliot Richardson</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President George Bush has added former U.S.
Attorney General Elliot Richardson of Massachusetts to his list of
endorsements in the Republican presidential primary.
   Bush supporters announced the endorsement Thursday at a news
conference in the historic Union Oyster House attended by New
Hampshire Gov. John Sununu and former Massachusetts Gov. Edward J.
King.
   Richardson, who served Massachusetts as attorney general and
held several Cabinet posts under Republican presidents, was
traveling in Japan. But Bush organizers issued a statement in which
Richardson praised Bush for his ``leadership ability'' and
``personal familiarity with the world's leaders.''
   State Sen. Paul Cellucci _ the Bush coordinator for
Massachusetts _ said the vice president welcomed the endorsement.
   ``We think it's going to give us a big boost as we move to Super
Tuesday,'' he said. According to recent polls, Bush leads Kansas
Sen. Bob Dole by about 20 percentage points in Massachusetts.
