<HEAD>Share Prices Rise In Early London Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices rose in early trading on the London
stock exchange today, continuing the market's recent upswing.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100 index was little changed
when the market officially opened at 9 a.m. up 0.1 points at
1,813.4.
   But it started rising immediately and at 9:45 a.m., the index
was up 7.8 points at 1,821.1.
   Enterprise Oil showed the largest gain, with the stock gaining
13 pence to 315 pence. Enterprise was boosted by rumors of a
successful drilling result on one of its North Sea permits.
   The early trend followed losses in New York Thursday, where the
Dow Jones industrial average fell 7.80 to 2,063.49, and gains in
Tokyo overnight, where the Nikkei index rose 19.12 to 25,615.43.
