<1ST_LINE>r a PM-TeddyBear-Fatal     03-04 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Teddy Bear-Fatal,0166</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Teddy Bear Buckled In, But Beltless Driver Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A driver who secured his teddy bear with a
seatbelt but failed to do the same for himself died after being
thrown from the car in a crash, authorities said.
   The 31-year-old victim, whose name was being withheld until his
family could be notified, died late Wednesday on the Long Beach
Freeway, said California Highway Patrol Officer Richard Perez.
   ``For unknown reasons, he drifted to the right and struck a
guardrail,'' Perez said. ``He went airborne about 35 feet and down
into a chain-link fence.''
   Paramedics pronounced the man dead at the scene, said CHP
dispatcher Ruth Frias.
   The teddy bear remained in the vehicle, Perez said.
   ``The investigating officer was telling me that (the driver) was
alone in the car, but he had a little teddy bear with him,'' Perez
said. ``He had the teddy bear seated in the passenger seat with a
belt on.''
</TEXT>
