<HEAD>Killer Crocs Devour Five Villagers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LUSAKA, Zambia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Crocodiles in Zambia's Kafue River have
devoured five people since the beginning of the year, and villagers
have asked the authorities to shoot the reptiles, a local official
said today.
   Dickson Ponde, chairman of Kasiba Ward council in the central
Copperbelt province, called for immediate action to stop the
crocodiles, which he said are attacking several people each week.
   The five deaths occurred since the beginning of the year. Ponde
made his plea to Rankin Sikasula, a senior member of President
Kenneth Kaunda's governing party, when he was inspecting a pontoon
bridge on the Kafue river.
   Sikasula promised that hunters will soon be sent to the area to
reduce the crocodile population.
