<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Theater-Blackout     03-04 0155</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Theater-Blackout,0160</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Electrical Problem Blacks Out Top London Musical</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An electrical problem struck a theater where the
musical ``Me and My Girl'' had just gotten under way, and the
audience of more than 1,000 had to be sent home when the show
couldn't go on.
   The problem at the Adelphi Theater on Thursday night developed
only 20 minutes into the show, as star Karl Howman was midway
through the title number, according to a statement from the theater.
   The unspecified problem couldn't be fixed immediately, the
statement said.
   Arrangements were being made to get the disappointed
theatergoers into other performances of the show, which is in its
fourth year playing to capacity crowds.
   ``Me and My Girl,'' about a Cockney from London's tough East End
who becomes an aristocrat, is a revival of the 1930s Noel Gay hit
which launched the song ``The Lambeth Walk'' that became part of
Cockney folklore.
</TEXT>
