<HEAD>White House Executive Chef Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hans Raffert, who joined the White House
kitchen staff 18 years ago, has been named to the top position of
executive chef, it was announced today.
   He is the first to have been promoted to the position from
within the ranks of the kitchen staff.
   Raffert has been acting executive chef since January, when Jon
Hill left after five months in the position.
   Raffert, 60, was born in Germany and is a naturalized American
citizen. He was hired as an assistant chef in 1969 during the Nixon
administration.
