<1ST_LINE>r a AM-FraternityOut     03-04 0302</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Fraternity Out,0310</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Frat Kicked off Penn Campus for Hiring Strippers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The University of Pennsylvania announced
Friday the 1{-year suspension of a fraternity that hired two black
strippers to perform at a party.
   Zeta Beta Tau ``will be permitted to return only if it meets
stringent requirements for its reorganization,'' said Penn
spokesman William Epstein.
   The exact terms have not been established, but Penn President
Sheldon Hackney said the first step is ``an immediate public
apology.''
   In a joint statement, Hackney and Provost Michael Aiken said the
charges against the fraternity ``were very serious and deserved the
significant sanctions that we are applying.''
   ``Behavior that dehumanizes any individual or group will not be
tolerated at Penn. Every one of us has a responsibility to help
build a community that values our diversity and the worth of each
individual.''
   Members of Zeta Beta Tau said that have been given until March
20 to move out. The 112-member, all-white fraternity will not be
allowed to pledge new members and will not be allowed to reapply
for recognition by the university until September 1989.
   ZBT President Zane Brown, in a statement, complained the
decision was unjust, but apologized for the rush party incident.
   The university charged the fraternity in February with engaging
in lewdness, indecent exposure and hazing through activities that
were ``indecent or shocking to moral or religious scruples.''
   The charges stemmed from a rush party in September, when two
black women stripped, performed sexually explicit acts and danced
naked with a prospective freshman pledge before an audience that
shouted racial epithets, according to the university.
   The fraternity had offered to pay a $2,500 fine to the campus
women's center, make a public apology and attend educational
programs on sexual harassment. But black student leaders said they
wanted ZBT expelled.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
