<HEAD>112 Apply for Dogcatcher Job</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUNTINGTON, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 100 people applied for the
$5-an-hour job of dogcatcher, a measure of the city's tough
economic times, says the director of the animal shelter.
   The Huntington Cabell Wayne Animal Shelter advertised for three
days last month for someone who is in good health and has a high
school diploma and driver's license. One hundred-twelve people
applied.
   ``I think the number of responses we got is a clear indication
of the need for jobs in this area,'' the shelter director, Pat
Thomas, said Thursday. ``I just wish I had 112 available jobs to
offer these people.''
   She said she hopes to fil the job next week.
