<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--Moose     03-04 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Moose,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Game Wardens' Effort to Save Moose Fails</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ERROL, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A young moose that had fallen through ice on
the Androscoggin River was destroyed Friday after a community
effort to save it failed.
   Volunteers and game wardens used blankets overnight in an effort
to keep the animal warm ``but she had suffered enough and couldn't
even lift her head. So I made the decision to destroy it,'' said
Fish and Game Warden Martin Garabedian.
   When an animal gets in trouble, Garabedian said, ``we usually
let nature take its course, but there were so many people who
wanted to help that we gave it a shot,'' adding that about 30
volunteers in the community of 300 people brought blankets.
   Garabedian on Thursday supervised the rescue of the 2-year-old,
600-pound moose.
   Garabedian said he looped a noose around the moose, and ``it
took seven or eight of us to pull her out.''
</TEXT>
