<HEAD>Bank Robbers' Haul: Coffee, Sugar, Mouthwash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TRENTON, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities are searching for a band of
crooks who broke into the First Jersey National Bank and stole
non-dairy creamer and mouthwash.
   And sugar. And coffee _ regular and decaf. And soda.
   The loot was valued at roughly $260.
   Police Sgt. Robert Orlowski said Friday that the bank was robbed
sometime late Monday or early Tuesday. The outlaws kicked in
several inner doors and made their way to the employees' supply
cabinet.
   When the thiefs departed, the bank was out 12 five-pound bags of
sugar, 24 boxes of tea, six cans of decaffeinated coffee, 12 cans
of regular coffee, 16 bottles of dish detergent, nine boxes of
non-dairy creamer, three bottles of mouthwash and three cases of
soda.
   Orlowski said there was no evidence the bandits even tried to
get to the vault.
   ``They must be big coffee drinkers. But I don't know what
they're going to do with 16 bottles of dish detergent,'' said
Orlowski.
