<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Hot Fudge,0127</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Here's the Scoop on `Hot' Fudge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KEARNEY, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Somebody swiped 360 cans of chocolate syrup
from a restaurant, and police have issued a statewide alert for
``hot'' fudge.
   ``We're looking for somebody with a lot of chocolate on their
face and a lot of acne,'' said Capt. Dan Lynch, who as of Friday
had no suspects.
   Don McBride, owner of the Dairy Queen restaurant, said the thief
or thieves cut a padlock to a storage area at mid-week and took
enough syrup to make more than 19,000 sundaes.
   McBride said the syrup, valued at $2,400, was apparently all the
intruders wanted.
   Police have notified authorities across the state that someone
may try to sell the stolen syrup.
</TEXT>
