<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union still is bombarding the U.S.
Embassy in Moscow with microwave radiation, more than four years
after U.S. officials protested a resumption of the tactic, the
State Department says.
   ``Microwave signals in the 5-11 GHz (gigahertz) range continue
to be detected at the Moscow embassy chancery,'' the department
