<HEAD>Southland Sells Reddy Ice Operation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Southland Corp. announced the sale of its Reddy
Ice operation to the investment firm Kaminski-Engles Capital Corp.
for an undisclosed amount of cash.
   Reddy Ice is the world's largest producer of fragmentary ice and
operates seven plants in Texas, Florida and Nevada.
   Most Reddy Ice employees will be retained after the sale, said
officials with Dallas-based Kaminski-Engles.
   Southland also said it plans to divest its Snack Foods and
Chemical-Food Labs divisions and other retail operations.
   Southland, the parent company of 7-Eleven convenience stores,
plans major asset sales to help pay off debt incurred in its $4.9
billion leveraged buyout. The company on Tuesday announced the sale
of 473 7-Eleven stores in 10 states to Circle K Corp., its chief
competitor, .
