<HEAD>Heileman To Sell Non-Brewing Assets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LA CROSSE, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bond Corp. Holdings Ltd., the Australian
company that bought the G. Heileman Brewing Co. last fall, has
decided to sell the brewer's bakery division, according to a letter
sent to employees.
   Michael D. Moon, president of the Heileman Baking Co., said in
the letter sent Thursday that the division was being offered to
sale ``to a wide variety of American and international companies
and investors.''
   About 4,700 people are employed nationwide at the division's 12
bakeries, which have annual sales of about $350 million.
   Moon said management had made an offer two weeks ago to buy the
bakeries. ``Our goal is continuity of the company and jobs for all
of its people,'' he said.
