<HEAD>Uruguay To Sign Refinancing Pact</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Uruguay is scheduled to sign a $1.8 billion
refinancing agreement with about 100 commercial banks on Friday,
bank officials said Thursday.
   The eight-member Bank Advisory Group for Uruguay said the pact
covers medium- and long-term external debt to commercial banks
maturing from Jan. 1, 1985 through Dec. 31, 1991.
   Uruguay currently has around $4.6 billion in outstanding debt,
of which $2.2 billion is with commercial banks.
   The terms of the refinancing agreement include an interest-rate
margin of seven-eighths to 1 percent over the London Interbank
Offered Rate, and maturities extending to the year 2004, the group
said.
