<HEAD>U.S. Postage Still Low, Relatively Speaking</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Despite the impending increase in U.S. postage
rates, mailing a first-class letter in this country remains among
the lowest in the industrialized world.
   Here is a list of postage rates for foreign nations, supplied by
the U.S. Postal Service, and their costs in U.S. funds.
   _Italy, 48.5 cents.
   _West Germany, 47.6 cents.
   _Japan, 46.9 cents.
   _Austria, 42.3 cents.
   _Norway, 42.2 cents.
   _Netherlands, 39.8 cents.
   _France, 38.8 cents.
   _Belgium, 37.1 cents.
   _Switzerland, 36.8 cents.
   _Sweden, 36.5 cents.
   _United Kingdom, 31.8 cents.
   _Canada, 28.9 cents.
   _Australia, 26.4 cents.
</TEXT>
